the German presidency in the EU. The novelty it brought to our political agenda, in our court, was Foreign Minister Džamír’s a-game. Prior to this, he actually had none. What should we expect from him? Since we are a small country and thus ineligible to assert our views, we should want our FM to act like an international statesman, a politician who knows how to act, but also to speak, in English. And that, even with János Martonyi. Of course, we can criticize him for his current role in the continuing judicial case about his son, sickeningly managed, and clearly unbecoming of a former minister. The question, however, remains—there is no other suitable person in the otherwise stellar party of the ruling SMER-SD, exactly SMER-SD of all the parties!

Look at the first post-vacation events—the SEF exhibition, ETPC, Bratislava Jazz Days, Heart of Darkness…

I believe the most significant event that happened to Slovakia in the past five years was the fall of communism. Mr. Putin is just the same as Mr. Lenin in his fully staged senselessness. His only talent being to justify the existence of Soros’ m-o-n-e-y!!!!!!!!!! Other than that, I would say that Porsche, even without Miss Diva, is rather a novelty than anything significant.
